   Jeff Allen and Perry Barndt are gamblers... their game, classic and exotic 
   cars. They travel the country looking to buy and sell cars. Whether it's a 
   rare Shelby Mustang or a one-of-a-kind Bugatti, the key is buy low and     
   sell high, something that doesn't always happen.                           
                                                                              
   Selling cars is a dangerous business... but perhaps there's no greater     
   danger than negotiating with your own dad. Tom Souter, Jeff's dad,         
   runs his own classic car dealership right around the corner from Jeff's    
   shop in Lubbock, Texas.                                                    
                                                                              
   They are not just regular trading partners; they are trading partners      
   hell-bent on one-upmanship. Tom says doing a deal with his son is like     
   being locked in a closet with a porcupine, "it's gonna hurt but you know   
   it won't kill you."
